headline.main: The Health Warden Judgement.; MOTION TO VACATE DENIED.

docs.lead_paragraph: Grant H. Adams vs. The Mayor, This case has been several times fully stated in the TIMES. The plaintiff was a Health Warden of the Eighteenth Ward, and was removed from office on the 15th of May, 1858, but still claimed title thereto, and brought his action for salary claimed subsequently to the date of his removal.
